gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 129, Rockets 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Kevin Durant put up his 1st triple-double of the season and 18th of his career with 27 points, 10 rebounds and a career-high tying 16 assists to lead the Suns over the Rockets, 129-113. Eric Gordon added 27 points and seven 3PM in the victory, while Alperen Sengun led the Rockets with 24 points and five rebounds in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 15-15 on the season, while the Rockets fall to 15-14.
